graph TD
    A[Start: Client has mental health issues interfering with work]

    A --> B{Does the client have a diagnosed mental health condition?}
    B --> B1[Yes]
    B --> B2[No]

    B1 --> C{What is the severity of the condition?}
    C --> C1[Mild to Moderate]
    C --> C2[Severe or Debilitating]

    C1 --> D{Is the client currently receiving treatment?}
    D --> D1[Yes]
    D1 --> E{Is treatment effectively managing symptoms?}
    E --> E1[Yes]
    E1 --> F{Is the client ready to seek employment or maintain current job?}
    F --> F1[Yes]
    F1 --> G{Does the client need workplace accommodations?}
    G --> G1[Yes]
    G1 --> H[Assist client in requesting reasonable accommodations under ADA]
    G --> G2[No]
    G2 --> I[Support client in job search or employment retention]

    F --> F2[No]
    F2 --> J[Provide career counseling; assess job readiness; consider gradual return]

    E --> E2[No]
    E2 --> K[Refer client back to mental health provider for treatment adjustment]

    D --> D2[No]
    D2 --> L{Is the client willing to access mental health services?}
    L --> L1[Yes]
    L1 --> M[Refer to appropriate mental health services; consider brief interventions]
    L --> L2[No]
    L2 --> N[Explore barriers to treatment; address concerns sensitively]

    C2 --> O{Is the client currently receiving intensive treatment?}
    O --> O1[Yes]
    O1 --> P[Coordinate with treatment team; focus on stabilization before employment]
    O --> O2[No]
    O2 --> Q{Is immediate intervention needed?}
    Q --> Q1[Yes]
    Q1 --> R[Facilitate urgent mental health evaluation; ensure safety]
    Q --> Q2[No]
    Q2 --> S[Refer to comprehensive mental health services]

    B2 --> T{Are there signs suggesting an undiagnosed mental health issue?}
    T --> T1[Yes]
    T1 --> U{Is the client open to a mental health assessment?}
    U --> U1[Yes]
    U1 --> V[Refer for assessment; monitor engagement]
    U --> U2[No]
    U2 --> W[Respect decision; provide information; monitor for changes]

    T --> T2[No]
    T2 --> X[Proceed with available information; address presenting issues]

    V & M & K & S & W & X & N & P & J --> Y{Assess impact on functioning and employment suitability}
    Y --> Y1{Match job options to client's abilities and challenges}
    Y1 --> Z[Identify suitable jobs; consider specific conditions]

    Z --> AA{Does the client need vocational rehabilitation or job training?}
    AA --> AA1[Yes]
    AA1 --> AB[Refer to vocational rehabilitation services]
    AA --> AA2[No]
    AA2 --> AC[Proceed with job placement support]

    AB & AC --> AD{Consider need for workplace accommodations or supports}
    AD --> AD1[Yes]
    AD1 --> AE[Assist in requesting accommodations; educate on rights]
    AD --> AD2[No]
    AD2 --> AF[Support client in employment process]

    AE & AF --> AG{Does the client have a support network?}
    AG --> AG1[Yes]
    AG1 --> AH[Encourage use of support network; connect with peer groups]
    AG --> AG2[No]
    AG2 --> AI[Connect client with community resources]

    AH & AI --> AJ{Monitor for co-occurring issues or changes in condition}
    AJ --> AK[Adjust Action Plan as needed; maintain regular contact]

    AK --> AL[End: Tailored Action Plan addressing mental health nuances]
